3. **MEASURE — the go/no-go.** Contiguous-region query, **bytes fetched + wall
   clock**, over a local HTTP server, three ways:
   - raw httpfs (positioned reads, no cache)
   - httpfs **+ `cache_httpfs` loaded** (block cache + parallel range IO)
   - download-to-temp (fetch whole `.pgen` once, open local)
   If range reads don't **decisively** beat download-to-temp, **stop** and ship
   download-to-temp instead — having spent a minimal shim, not a finished fork.

4. **Only if green:** complete the fixpoint patch set, region range-coalescing via
   the in-memory offset index, `.pgi` on the shim, config gate, drift-canary +
